    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Trigger Settings Control
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Trigger settings define when an Event Point activates. Some event points activate as soon as
        the mission starts, while others wait for the player to enter a radius, complete another
        event, use an object, kill or arrest a target, finish a conversation, or satisfy a counter
        condition.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Trigger settings are what turn individual Event Points into mission logic. A single event
        point can create an object, display a message, start a timer, or end the mission, but the
        trigger decides when that action actually happens.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_triggers_settings_panel.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TRIGGER TYPES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Triggered By Options
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">None / Game Starts</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">The Event Point is active from the start of the mission, or triggers immediately when the mission begins.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Dependency</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when another referenced Event Point has triggered or activated. Uses an Event Point reference.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Player Enters Radius</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the player enters this Event Point’s radius. Uses the Radius field.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Door Opens</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when an associated door or openable object is opened. Usually tied to nearby or linked door logic.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Tripwire</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a tripwire-style area or line is crossed.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Pressure Pad</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a pressure pad is activated, usually by the player, person, or thing standing on it.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Electric Fence</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers from electric fence interaction or state. This appears to be legacy or special-case mission logic.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Water Level</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers based on water level or environmental state. This appears to be special-case environment logic.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Security Camera</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers from security camera detection or camera state.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Switch</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a switch is used or activated.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Anim Prim</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers from an animated prim or object state.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Timer</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers after a timer delay. Uses the time or radius-style numeric field depending on editor mapping.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Shout (all)</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when all required shout conditions in range are satisfied. Uses radius/text-style trigger data.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Boolean AND</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers only when two referenced Event Points or conditions are both true. Uses EPRef and EPRefBool.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Boolean OR</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when either of two referenced Event Points or conditions is true. Uses EPRef and EPRefBool.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Item Held / Specific Item Held / Item Seen</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when an item is held, a specific item is held, or an item is seen/detected.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Killed or Arrested / Killed Not Arrested / Person Arrested</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers based on the state of a referenced person, such as killed, arrested, or specifically killed but not arrested.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Shout (any)</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when any matching shout condition occurs in range.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Countdown Timer / Visible Countdown Timer</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a countdown completes. Visible Countdown Timer shows the countdown to the player and is the timer type targeted by Extend Timer.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Enemy Enters Radius</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when an enemy or person enters this Event Point’s radius. Often uses both an EP reference and Radius.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Player Enters Cuboid</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the player enters a box or cuboid region instead of a circular radius.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Target 50% Damaged / Half Dead</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the referenced target, person, or object reaches roughly half health or damage.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Group Dead</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when all relevant members of a group or colour are dead.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Enemy Sees Person</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when one referenced enemy/person sees another referenced person. Uses two Event Point references.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Player Uses Person / Player Uses in Radius</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the player interacts with a referenced person or presses use while inside the Event Point’s radius.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Prim Damaged</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a prim or object is damaged.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Conversation Finished</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the referenced Conversation Event Point has completed.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Counter Reaches Value</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a mission counter reaches a configured value. Used with Increment and Reset Counter logic.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Crime Rate Above / Crime Rate Below</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the mission or world crime rate rises above or drops below a threshold.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Person Is Murderer</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers if the referenced person is marked as the murderer.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Person In Vehicle</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when a referenced person is in a referenced vehicle. Uses two Event Point references.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Thing Stop Direction/Radius / Radius and Direction / Move Radius Direction</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Movement, proximity, and direction-related triggers, likely used by moving objects, path logic, or directional checks.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Player Carries Person</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the player is carrying the referenced person.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Random</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Random chance trigger, usually dependent on a referenced Event Point or condition.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Player Fires a Gun</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Triggers when the player fires a weapon.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Darci Has Grabbed Someone / Darci Punches and Kicks</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Character-specific triggers for Darci grabbing someone or attacking with punches and kicks.</Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- LISTENING MODE -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Listening Mode
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Listening Mode controls what happens after an Event Point has been triggered. The practical
        difference is mostly about whether the event point remains true for dependency chains,
        remains true only while the trigger is happening, stays active temporarily, or dies after
        firing.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_triggers_listening_mode.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">None</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">No listening mode set. In the original editor this is effectively invalid/default and is usually forced to Active.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Active</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Activates once, then stays active for the rest of the mission. This is the normal “trigger once and remain true” mode.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Active While</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Activates whenever its trigger condition is currently true. It is true only while the condition is happening.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Active Time</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Activates when triggered, then remains active only for a fixed time using the AfterTimer value.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Active Die</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Activates once, then becomes dead/inactive afterwards. Useful for one-shot actions that should not remain active as a dependency and should not trigger again.</Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Practical summary:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Active = “I happened, and I stay true.”
                    Active While = “I am true only while the condition is true.”
                    Active Time = “I become true for X time, then turn off.”
                    Active Die = “I fire once, then remove/kill myself as a useful trigger.”
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>
</FlowDocument>
